com.nequissimus.university.k1584.data

Class BiMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.nequissimus.university.k1584.data.BiMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key type
    V - Value type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class BiMap<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<K,V>
    Bidirectional map that allows retrieval in both directions. Since this map is implemented by using two HashMaps internally, the user needs to ensure the uniqueness of all keys and values. Otherwise there may be discrepancies when retrieving via values.
